text.tspan: OSGeoLive is a self-contained bootable DVD, USB thumb
drive or Virtual Machine based on Lubuntu, that allows you to
try a wide variety of open source geospatial software without
installing anything. It is composed entirely of free software,
allowing it to be freely distributed, duplicated
It provides pre-configured applications for a range of
geospatial use cases, including viewing, storage, publishing,
analysis and manipulation of data. It also contains sample
50+ Free and Open Source Geospatial Applications
Documentation for software, standards and data
Try it! It is really simple...
Insert DVD or USB thumb drive in your computer or start
Reboot the computer. Verify boot device order if necessary.
Not necessary for the virtual machine
Select and run applications from the Geospatial menu
Your first contact with Open Source Software for Geospatial
GRASS GIS, gvSIG, OpenJUMP GIS, QGIS, SAGA
MapServer, MapProxy, ncWMS, pycsw, QGIS Server,
pgRouting, PostGIS, Rasdaman, SpatiaLite, Open Data Cube
GpsPrune, Marble, OpenStreetMap, iD editor, JOSM,
GMT, Mapnik, OTB, R for Spatial Data, Jupyter Notebook
Natural Earth, NetCDF Data Set, OpenStreetMap,
OSGeo North Carolina, USA Educational dataset
GEOS, GeoTools, GDAL, JTS Topology Suite, Proj
Since OSGeoLive is an Operating System could be used as
your mainly OS, but its main purpose is to show the wide
variety of open source geospatial software. Starting from
2008 OSGeoLive was used or presented all over the world
